                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799" calendar="Gregorian">18th
                                cent.</origDate><origPlace> Ethiopia.</origPlace>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>Ethiopia</provenance>
                        <acquisition> The manuscript was purchased by <persName
                                key="person_18157193" role="fmo">William Simpson</persName>, an
                            illustrator for the Illustrated London News and member of the <date calendar="Gregorian">1868</date>
                            Napier expedition to <origPlace>Magdala</origPlace>. According to a
                            note on the <locus from="i" to="i">inside front cover</locus>, <persName
                                key="person_18157193" role="fmo">William Simpson</persName>, ,
                            whose monogram is also included, obtained it from an Ethiopian as the
                            troops returned to Aden after the defeat of <persName
                                key="person_280993109">Tewodros</persName> II: “This book of
                            Devotion, 350 or 400, years old, I bought from an Abyssinnian [sic], at
                            the tent door, during the return march from <origPlace>Magdala</origPlace>, <date calendar="Gregorian"
                                >1868</date>”. The seller
                            may have been either <persName key="" role="fmo scr">Waldä Giyorgis</persName> or
                                <persName key="" role="fmo">Śarḍa Māryām</persName>, both of whose names
                            appear in the manuscript.</acquisition>
                    </history>
